title: Wes Montgomery & Clark Terry - 1992 - Straight, No Chaser FL
description:
Wes Montgomery & Clark Terry - 1992 - Straight, No Chaser

Wes Montgomery can surely be called the most influential guitarist in the last thirty years - his playing, original and Blues-inspired with phenomenal overblowing technique, has helped to pave the road to the development of Jazz and popular music. He has only visited Europe once in his relatively short, ten-year long recording career, having had performed in Hamburg, Recklinghausen (the Ruhrfestspiele Music Festival), and Paris in early '65. And so it only follows suit that the new tapes from this tour are an absolute collector's item.


01. Straight, No Chaser
02. Just Friends
03. In a Mellow Tone
04. We Got Rhythm
05. The Theme

Personnel:
Wes Montgomery - g
Clark Terry - tp
Harold Mabern - p
Arthur Harper - b
Jimmy Lovelace - dr
